China's 'Dalifornia,' a bohemian haven for young people searching for meaning
description: In the southern Yunnan province, Dali is the city of those who say 'no' in silence. This somewhat hipster haven has welcomed more and more young people eager to escape the crushing megacities of a country where growth is sputtering. This gentle form of opposition has not gone unnoticed by the authorities.

description: Antoine Renard, director of the World Food Programme in Palestine, is calling for a ceasefire in Gaza, a territory the UN warns is facing 'widespread famine.' He describes the impossible conditions under which the UN agency is carrying out its mission.

headline: Pope's 'Jubilee of Youth' with over a million attendees closes with Rome mass
description: Pope Leo held a final mass in Rome on Sunday, the culmination of a week-long youth pilgrimage that welcomed over a million Catholics from across the world. 'Aspire to great things, to holiness, wherever you are. Do not settle for less,' he told the young people.

headline: 'Struggling' Léon Marchand targets second gold at swimming worlds
description: The French superstar said his performance 'worries' him ahead of Sunday night's final, after qualifying for the 400m individual medley with an uncharacteristically sluggish swim.

description: 'Chefs' Gardens' (4/5). On his estate in eastern Riquewihr, this Alsatian chef cultivates plants that give the dishes at his restaurant, La Table du Gourmet, their unique flavor.

description: 'Being 20 in West Berlin' (6/6). In the late 1970s, as English pop dominated the world, Mark Reeder instead swore by German electronic music. He left his native Manchester at 20 to discover Berlin, its clubs and its music.

headline: In Brazil, Lula resists pressure from the Trump administration
description: Washington has wielded the threat of 50% tariffs against Brazil to influence the Brazilian judiciary, condemning what it calls a 'witch hunt' against former far-right President Jair Bolsonaro.

headline: Trial ordered for deadly 1982 attack on Paris Jewish restaurant
description: Two alleged members of a Palestinian militant group will stand trial in Paris over the attack that killed six in a restaurant in the city’s historic Marais district. Four other suspects remain under arrest warrants.
